-- Vodafone Ordered to Suspend Egyptian Mobile-Phone Services in Some Areas
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   B r o w n i n g
-- 2011-01-28T11:22:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-01-28/vodafone-ordered-to-suspend-egyptian-mobile-phone-services-in-some-areas.html
  Vodafone Group Plc  said it was
instructed to suspend mobile-phone services in  Egypt  in selected
areas.  “Under Egyptian legislation, the authorities have the
right to issue such an order and we are obliged to comply with
it,” Vodafone said in an e-mailed statement. “All mobile
operators in Egypt have been instructed to suspend services in
selected areas.”  The Egyptian authorities will be clarifying the situation
in due course, Vodafone said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Simon Thiel at 
 sthiel1@bloomberg.net  